you&#39;re facing this problem because `Metadata schemaMetadata` is a local variable and it&#180;s being replaced.

You can mock the `mediator.getMetadata` call to return the mock with a created Metadata object.
I have a lot of cases like this and normally I use it.

Mock this:

    mediator.getMetadata(scopeId, messageToBeDeleted.getTimestamp().getTime());

this way:

    when(mediator.getMetadata(any(), any()).thenReturn(new Metadata(){{
       setDataIndexName(&quot;IndexName&quot;):
    }};);

obviously, you need to mock the `mediator` before using when.

It works for me, I hope it helps you too.

